Library: com.hyperxtalk.macoscontacts

Type: library

Title: macOS Contacts

Summary: Provides access to the macOS Contacts framework (CNContactStore).

version: 1.0.0

author: HyperXTalk


Name: contactsGroups

Type: handler

Syntax: contactsGroups()

Summary: Returns a List of Arrays, each with keys "name" and "identifier".




Name: contactsFetchByPhone

Type: handler

Syntax: contactsFetchByPhone(<pPhone>)

Summary: Returns all contacts and filters locally for phone number containing pPhone.


Parameters:
:




Name: contactsRequestAccessGlue

Type: handler

Syntax: contactsRequestAccessGlue()

Summary: Request Contacts access via the native ObjC glue on the main thread.

Description:
Bypasses the LCB ObjC bridge for the permission call.
    Fires "accessRequestComplete" on the caller when the user responds.



Name: contactsFetchByGroup

Type: handler

Syntax: contactsFetchByGroup(<pGroupIdentifier>)

Summary: Returns a List of contact Arrays for all contacts in the given group.


Parameters:
:




Name: contactsAccessPoll

Type: handler

Syntax: contactsAccessPoll()

Summary: Poll the result of a pending contacts access request.

Returns: -1 if still pending, 0 if denied, 1 if granted.

Description: Call from a LiveCode Script timer until non-negative.




Name: contactsFetchAll

Type: handler

Syntax: contactsFetchAll()

Summary: Returns a List of Arrays, one per contact.

Description:
Each array has keys: identifier, givenName, familyName,
    fullName, organizationName, emailAddresses (List), phoneNumbers (List), note.



Name: contactsFetchByName

Type: handler

Syntax: contactsFetchByName(<pName>)

Summary: Returns contacts whose full name contains pName.


Parameters:
:




Name: contactsAuthorizationStatus

Type: handler

Syntax: contactsAuthorizationStatus()

Summary: Returns the current authorization status without prompting the user.

Returns: "granted", "denied", "restricted", or "not determined"




Name: contactsInitialize

Type: handler

Syntax: contactsInitialize()

Summary: Must be called once before contactsRequestAccess to set up the block pointer.

Description: Primes the CNContactStore instance. Returns true on success.




Name: contactsDiagnostic

Type: handler

Syntax: contactsDiagnostic()

Summary: Posts "contactsDiagnostic" to the caller with a step-by-step status string.

Description: Use this to identify exactly where initialisation or access request fails.




Name: contactsDelete

Type: handler

Syntax: contactsDelete(<pIdentifier>)

Summary: Deletes the contact with the given identifier.


Parameters:
:




Name: contactsUpdate

Type: handler

Syntax: contactsUpdate(<pIdentifier>,<pArray>)

Summary: Updates the contact with pIdentifier using fields from pArray.


Parameters:
:


:




Name: contactsCreate

Type: handler

Syntax: contactsCreate(<pArray>)

Summary: Creates a new contact from pArray.

Description:
pArray keys: givenName, familyName, organizationName,
    emailAddresses, phoneNumbers, note.

Returns: The new contact's identifier string, or empty on failure.


Parameters:
:




Name: contactsFetchByEmail

Type: handler

Syntax: contactsFetchByEmail(<pEmail>)

Summary: Returns contacts with an email address matching pEmail.


Parameters:
:




Name: contactsRequestAccess

Type: handler

Syntax: contactsRequestAccess()

Summary: Presents the system permission dialog if not yet determined.

Description:
Returns immediately. When the user responds, posts
    "accessRequestComplete" with a Boolean parameter to the caller.
    If status is already determined, returns the current status without
    showing a dialog and without posting a message.

Returns: "granted", "denied", "restricted", or "not determined"




